## 13. YOMITAN ZIP FORMAT SPECIFICATION

```
yomitan_dictionary.zip
├── index.json                 # Metadata
├── tag_bank_1.json           # Tag definitions
├── term_bank_1.json          # 10,000 term entries max
├── term_bank_2.json          # (if > 10,000 entries)
├── img/
│   ├── c123.jpg
│   ├── c456.png
│   └── ...
```

### index.json

```json
{
  "title": "GSM Character Dictionary",
  "revision": "2026020301",
  "format": 3,
  "author": "GameSentenceMiner",
  "description": "Character names from visual novels",
  "downloadUrl": "https://example.com/api/yomitan-dict?source=vndb&id=v17&spoiler_level=0",
  "indexUrl": "https://example.com/api/yomitan-index?source=vndb&id=v17&spoiler_level=0",
  "isUpdatable": true
}
```

### term_bank_1.json

Each entry is an array:
```json
[
  ["須々木 心一", "すずきしんいち", "name main", "", 100, [{...}], 0, ""],
  ["須々木", "すずき", "name main", "", 100, [{...}], 0, ""],
  ...
]
```

Format: [term, reading, definitionTags, rules, score, definitions, sequence, termTags]

---

## 14. CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

### Name Handling

**VNDB Name Order:**
- `name`: Western order "Given Family" (e.g., "Shinichi Suzuki")
- `original`: Japanese order "Family Given" (e.g., "須々木 心一")

**When generating readings from romanized name, swap order to Japanese:**
```
Romanized: "Shinichi Suzuki" (parts[0]=Given, parts[1]=Family)
Japanese: "須々木 心一" (family=須々木, given=心一)

Map:
- parts[0] (Shinichi) → Given reading (しんいち) → Japanese given
- parts[1] (Suzuki) → Family reading (すずき) → Japanese family
```

### Spoiler Filtering

- **Level 0 (No Spoilers):** Name, image, game, role only
- **Level 1 (Minor Spoilers):** + description (spoiler tags stripped), + stats
- **Level 2 (Full Spoilers):** + full description, + all traits with spoiler metadata

### Image Handling

1. Download from VNDB/AniList URL
2. Resize to 80x100 pixels
3. Encode as base64 with data URI: `data:image/jpeg;base64,...`
4. Store in ZIP as `img/c{char_id}.jpg`

### Rate Limiting

- VNDB: 200 requests per 5 minutes (200ms between pages)
- AniList: 90 requests per minute (300ms between pages)

